== About Me
I am a first year graduate student in Electrical Engineering and Computer Sciences (EECS) at UC Berkeley, advised by Professor [http://rfic.eecs.berkeley.edu/~niknejad/ Ali Niknejad] of the [https://bwrc.eecs.berkeley.edu/ Berkeley Wireless Research Center (BWRC)] and Professor [https://radonc.ucsf.edu/mekhail-anwar Mekhail Anwar] of the [https://radonc.ucsf.edu/ UCSF Department of Radiation Oncology]. Broadly speaking, I am interested in developing integrated circuits and systems to enable better diagnostic monitoring of general health and disease pathologies (like cancer). Towards this end, I am currently working on a project that aims to leverage radiation from clinical radionuclides to power medical implants. \n

I also attended UC Berkeley as an undergraduate, and studied EECS then as well. As an undergraduate, I worked within Professor [https://maharbizgroup.wordpress.com/ Michel Maharbiz's research group] to optimize the performance of piezoelectric transducers used for power harvesting and communication in ultrasonic medical implants. During this time, I was happy to be supervised by Drs. [https://maharbizgroup.wordpress.com/members/ Soner Sonmezoglu and Konlin Shen]. \n

